Here’s an updated `.gitignore` file that includes additional exclusions for common files and directories you might want to ignore. I’ve added entries for **macOS**, **Node.js/npm**, **system files**, and some other potential files you may encounter.

```gitignore
# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# C extensions
*.so

# Distribution / packaging
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
share/python-wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST

# PyInstaller
*.manifest
*.spec

# Installer logs
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt

# Unit test / coverage reports
htmlcov/
.tox/
.nox/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.cache
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml
*.cover
*.py,cover
.hypothesis/
.pytest_cache/
cover/

# Translations
*.mo
*.pot

# Django stuff
*.log
local_settings.py
db.sqlite3
db.sqlite3-journal

# Flask stuff
instance/
.webassets-cache

# Scrapy stuff
.scrapy

# Sphinx documentation
docs/_build/

# PyBuilder
.pybuilder/
target/

# Jupyter Notebook
.ipynb_checkpoints

# IPython
profile_default/
ipython_config.py

# Environments
.env
.venv
env/
venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/

# Spyder project settings
.spyderproject
.spyproject

# Rope project settings
.ropeproject

# mkdocs documentation
/site

# mypy
.mypy_cache/
.dmypy.json
dmypy.json

# Pyre type checker
.pyre/

# pytype static type analyzer
.pytype/

# Cython debug symbols
cython_debug/

# macOS specific files
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Thumbnails
._*

# macOS folder attributes
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
.VolumeIcon.icns
.AppleDB
.AppleDesktop
Network Trash Folder
Temporary Items
.apdisk

# Node.js
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*
.npm/

# VS Code
.vscode/

# IDEs and Editors
.idea/
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project

# System files
*.log
*.bak
*.swp
*~
*#
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Python version control files
.python-version

# pipenv
Pipfile.lock

# poetry
poetry.lock

# pdm
.pdm.toml

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/David-OConnor/pyflow and github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

# Celery
celerybeat-schedule
celerybeat.pid

# SageMath parsed files
*.sage.py

# PyCharm
# Uncomment to ignore the entire idea folder
#.idea/
```

### Explanation of Additional Entries
- **macOS files**: `.DS_Store`, `.AppleDouble`, etc. These are macOS-specific files that should generally be ignored.
- **Node.js files**: `node_modules/`, `npm-debug.log*`, etc. These are specific to Node.js and npm/yarn, which can often be generated in Python projects that use JavaScript/TypeScript for frontend development.
- **System files**: Temporary, swap, and log files, along with other system-specific clutter (like `Thumbs.db` on Windows).
- **IDE files**: `.vscode/`, `.idea/`, etc. to ignore files from editors like VS Code and PyCharm.

Adding these to your `.gitignore` file should help prevent unnecessary files from being included in your Git repository.
